'''Caleta Zorra''', meaning 'Bay of foxes' in [[Spanish language|Spanish]], is an enclosed, half-moon shaped [[inlet]] on the Pacific coast of [[Chiloé Island]] in [[Los Lagos Region|Los Lagos]] region, southern [[Chile]]. Lies north of [[Punta Pabellion]], it is located among [[Punta Zorra]] and [[Punta Barranco]].<ref>ProStar Publications. 2004. Prostar Sailing Directions 2004 West Coast of South America Enroute. page=119. retrieved on 12-05-2014</ref> The nearest residential area is the township of [[Puerto Carmen]].<ref>http://www.mbendi.com/a_sndmsg/facility.asp?I=203709.retrieved on 12-05-2014</ref>
==Environment==
Areas surrounding the cove is rich in natural environments. Whales such as [[Blue Whale]]s and [[Fin Whale]] swim just off the bay.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mPa4_y3cpS0</ref> Possibly, coast-loving whales such as [[Humpback Whale]]s or [[Southern Right Whale]]s occasionally take rests in the sheltered bay.
