[[File:Nawab's Dilkusha Garden, Dhaka (1904).jpg|thumb|240px|Nawab's Dilkusha Garden, Dhaka (1904) by Fritz Kapp.]]
'''Dilkusha''' is the commercial center of [[Dhaka]], the capital of [[Bangladesh]].<ref>[http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Dilkusha Dilkusha] in Banglapedia</ref> It is a part of the larger [[Motijheel]] area in the city. Historically, the [[Nawab of Dhaka|Nawabs of Dhaka]] used to have a garden palace here in the 19th and early 20th century. Dilkusha was the name of that palace.

