'''Johann Georg Heinrich Hassel''' (30 December 1770 in [[Wolfenbüttel]] &ndash; 18 January 1829 in [[Weimar]]) was a [[Germans|German]] [[geographer]] and [[statistician]]. He was an influential figure in the early 19th century and published several large books of [[geography]] and [[statistics]]. Hassel was elected a Foreign Honorary Member of the [[American Academy of Arts and Sciences]] in 1828.<ref name=AAAS>{{cite web|title=Book of Members, 1780–2010: Chapter H|url=http://www.amacad.org/publications/BookofMembers/ChapterH.pdf|publisher=American Academy of Arts and Sciences|accessdate=8 September 2016}}</ref>

