{{Infobox book || name = Gruhabanga |image = Gruhabhanga cover.jpg |image_size = 220px |caption = |author = [[Bhyrappa|S L Bhyrappa]] |country = [[India]] |language = [[Kannada language|Kannada]] |genre = [[Novel]] |publisher = Sahitya Bhandara, [[Bangalore]] |release_date = 1970 |media_type = Print ([[Paperback]] & [[Hardcover|Hardback]]) |preceded_by = [[Tabbaliyu Neenade Magane]] (1968) |followed_by = [[Nirakarana]] (1971) |isbn = |dewey= |congress= |oclc= |website = [http://slbhyrappa.in/grihabhanga/ ''Official website''] }}
'''''Grahabanga''''' ({{lang-kn|ಗೃಹಭಂಗ}} is a well-known novel by one of the most important novelists in Kannada [[Bhyrappa|S L Bhyrappa]]. The plot depicts rural India, starts around the 1920s and ends around the 1940s. The story has the heroic struggle of a woman against her idiotic husband, vicious mother-in-law, superstitious neighbours and pervading poverty. [[Tiptur]], [[Channarayapatna]] regions are covered in this novel. This novel is considered an Indian classic and hence [[National Book Trust]], India translated this into all the [[languages of India|fourteen major languages of India]]. In 2003 it was made into a television series by [[Girish Kasaravalli]] which was produced by the actress [[Soundarya]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17860158-gruhabanga?ac=1|title=Gruhabanga}}</ref>
