{{unreferenced|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox park | name = Maputo Special Reserve | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | type = | location = [[Mozambique]] | coords = <!-- {{Coord|NNNNN|NNNNN|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | area = | created = 1932 <!-- {{Start date|YYYY}} --> | operator = | visitation_num = | status = }} '''Maputo Special Reserve''', (formerly known as Maputo Elephant Reserve), is a nature reserve in [[Mozambique]]. The reserve is located on [[Maputo Bay]], approximately 100 kilometers southeast of the city of [[Maputo, Mozambique]]. The Reserve is {{convert|77400|ha|acre}} in extent and was originally proclaimed in 1932. The reserve will eventually form part of the [[Lubombo Transfrontier Conservation Area]], which includes national parks from [[South Africa]], [[Mozambique]] and [[Swaziland]]. At the moment it forms part of the [[Usuthu-Tembe-Futi Transfrontier Conservation Area]].
==Habitats== {{Empty section|date=July 2010}}
==Fauna== Includes 350 [[African elephant]]s, Birds (Kingfisher, Fish Eagle and many more), [[zebra]], [[antelope]], [[crocodile]]s, [[Hippopotamus|hippos]], small bucks (red duiker, suni, reedbuck and steenbok).
