==Prior to 20th century== {{History of Mauritius}}
* 1721 - French in power on [[Isle de France (Mauritius)|Isle de France]]; Noord-Wester Haven (harbor) renamed "Port Louis."{{sfn|Nave|2005}} * 1729 - Hôtel du Gouvernement built.<ref name=traces2017>{{citation |title=L'hôtel du gouvernement: sur les traces des élus |work= Lexpress.mu |language=fr |url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/305445/lhotel-gouvernement-sur-traces-elus |date= 24 April 2017 }}</ref> * 1735 - Development of Port Louis begins (approximate date).<ref name=MCCPL>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923085751/http://www.mccpl.mu/ct_history.html |url=http://www.mccpl.mu/ct_history.html |deadurl=yes |archivedate= 23 September 2017 |title=History of the City |work= Mccpl.mu |publisher= City Council of Port Louis }}</ref> * 1749 - [[State House (Mauritius)|Le Réduit]] (fort) built near Port Louis at [[Moka]]. * 1772 - Bagne Prison built.<ref name=half2008>{{citation |url= https://www.lexpress.mu/article/port-louis-home-half-our-national-heritage |work=Lexpress.mu |date=25 August 2008 |title=Port Louis: Home to half of our national heritage |author=Satyendra Peerthum }}. [https://www.lexpress.mu/article/port-louis-home-half-our-national-heritage-0 Part 2], 1 September 2008</ref> * 1782 - {{illm|Dyot Canal|sv|Dyot Canal}} construction begins.<sup>([[:de:Liste der Kulturdenkmäler in Mauritius|de]])</sup> * 1790 - Thomas Enouf becomes mayor.<ref name=MCCPL /> * 1794 - Town renamed “Port de La Montagne.”<ref name=MCCPL /> * 1795 - Town renamed “Port Nord-Ouest.”<ref name=MCCPL /> * 1803 - Town renamed “Port Napoléon.”<ref name=MCCPL /> * 1805 - Mosque constructed.{{sfn|Nave|2005}} * 1810 ** British in power.<ref name=MCCPL /> ** Town renamed "Port Louis" again.<ref name=MCCPL /> ** Population: 24,000.{{sfn|Nave|2005}} * 1812 - [[Champ de Mars Racecourse]] opens.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2013}} * 1816 - Fire.<ref name=traces2017 /> * 1838 - {{illm|Citadel of Port-Louis (Mauritius)|fr|Citadelle de Port-Louis (Maurice)|lt=Citadel}} built.<ref name=britannica /> * 1847 - [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Port-Louis]] established.<ref>{{cite web |title=Chronology of Catholic Dioceses: Mauritius |url= http://www.katolsk.no/organisasjon/verden/chronology/mauritius |publisher=[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Oslo]] |location=Norway |accessdate= 23 September 2017 }}</ref> * 1849 - Development of [[Aapravasi Ghat]] immigration depot begins.<ref name=britannica /> * 1850 ** February: Municipal election held.<ref name=Express2006 /> ** March: Louis Léchelle becomes mayor.<ref>{{cite book |title=Mauritius Almanac and Colonial Register |year=1874 |chapter= Municipality of Port Louis: List of mayors and deputy-mayors from 1850 |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=EMcNAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA213 }}</ref> * 1852 - [[Jummah Mosque (Mauritius)|Mosquée des Arabes]] established. * 1864 - North line [[History of rail transport in Mauritius|railway]] begins operating.{{cn|date=September 2017}} * 1866 - Municipal government headquartered in the Hôtel d’Europe building.<ref name=Express2006>{{citation |title=Il y a 150 ans, P.-Louis perdait son 1er maire |work= [[L'Express (Mauritius)|Lexpress.mu]] |language=fr |url=https://www.lexpress.mu/article/il-y-150-ans-p-louis-perdait-son-1er-maire |date=24 April 2006 }}</ref> * 1867 - Malaria outbreak. * 1870 - General Post Office built.<ref name=half2008 /> * 1869 - Port Louis economy affected by opening of [[Suez Canal]] in Egypt.{{sfn|Nave|2005}} * 1887 - ''Revue historique et littéraire de l'Ile Maurice'' begins publication. * 1892 - 29 April: {{illm|1892 Mauritius cyclone|de|Zyklon in Mauritius 1892}} occurs.<ref name=Haydn1910 /> * 1897 - 22 June: [[List of statues of Queen Victoria|Statue]] of British queen Victoria unveiled.<ref name=Haydn1910>{{Citation |publisher = Ward, Lock & Co. |publication-place = London |title = [[Haydn's Dictionary of Dates]] |author = Benjamin Vincent |edition = 25th |publication-date = 1910 |chapter= Mauritius |chapterurl = https://hdl.handle.net/2027/uc2.ark:/13960/t41r6xh8t?urlappend=%3Bseq=905 }}</ref>
==20th century== * 1904 - 8-9 June: Flood.<ref name=Haydn1910 /> * 1907 - Population: 30,899.<ref>{{cite book|title=Blue Book for the Colony of Mauritius: 1907 |oclc=18922692 |location=Port Louis |url= https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/008607947 |via=[[HathiTrust]] |year=1908}}</ref> * 1910 - [[Government Houses of the British Empire and Commonwealth|Government House]] rebuilt.<ref name=traces2017 /> * 1919 - Population: 40,106 metro.<ref>{{cite book |title=[[Statesman's Year-Book]] |year=1921 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= British Empire: Mauritius |chapterurl= https://hdl.handle.net/2027/njp.32101072368440?urlappend=%3Bseq=244 }}</ref> * 1933 - Catholic [[St. Louis Cathedral, Port-Louis|St. Louis Cathedral]] rebuilt. * 1942 - [[Sir Seewoosagur Ramgoolam International Airport|Airport]] established in [[Plaine Magnien]], 48 km from Port Louis. * 1952 - Population: 84,539.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1950_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1955 |year= |publisher=[[Statistical Office of the United Nations]] |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 or more inhabitants |pages=171-184 }}</ref> * 1953 - Mauritius Sugar Industry Research Institute founded in nearby [[Réduit (Mauritius)|Réduit]].<ref name=britannica />[http://www.msiri.mu/index.php?langue=eng&rub=221] * 1959 - [[Eddy J. Changkye]] becomes mayor. * 1963 - ''[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]]'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name=Europa2004 /> * 1964 - Population: 126,550 (estimate).<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1960_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1965 |year=1966 |publisher=[[Statistical Office of the United Nations]] |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=140-161 }}</ref> * 1965 - [[University of Mauritius]] established in nearby Réduit.<ref name=britannica /> * 1966 ** City Hall built. ** {{illm|Musée de la Photographie (Mauritius)|fr|lt=Photography museum}} founded.[http://www.musee-photo.voyaz.com/Web_pages/introduction.htm] * 1967 - City economy affected by temporary closure of Suez Canal during war in Egypt.<ref name=britannica>{{cite web |url= https://www.britannica.com/place/Port-Louis |accessdate= 23 September 2017 |work= Encyclopædia Britannica |title= Port Louis }}</ref> * 1968 - Mauritian independence.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2013}} * 1969 - Six administrative wards created.<ref name=MCCPL /> * 1975 - Suez Canal reopens in Egypt.<ref name=britannica /> * 1979 - August: Sugar industry labor strike.<ref name=Europa2001>{{cite book|publisher=[[Europa Publications]] |title=Political Chronology of Africa |series=Political Chronologies of the World |year= 2001 |isbn=0203409957 |chapter=Mauritius |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=0O86sZdHfHUC }}</ref> * 1984 - Population: 135,200 (estimate).<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1980_round.htm |title=1985 Demographic Yearbook |year=1987 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=247-289 }}</ref> * 1989 - [[Stock Exchange of Mauritius]] headquartered in city.<ref name=bbc>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-13882731 |accessdate= 23 September 2017 |title= Mauritius profile: Timeline |work= [[BBC News]] }}</ref> * 1992 ** [[Mauritius Telecom]] headquartered in city.<ref name=Europa2004>{{cite book |title=Africa South of the Sahara 2004 |series=Regional Surveys of the World |publisher= [[Europa Publications]] |isbn= 1857431839 |chapter= Mauritius: Directory |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=jj4J-AXGDaQC |year=2004 }}</ref> ** City becomes part of independent [[Republic of Mauritius]].{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2013}} * 1993 ** October: Meeting of the [[Organisation internationale de la Francophonie]] held in city. ** Meeting of the [[Association Internationale des Maires Francophones]] held in city. * 1995 - {{illm|Mauritius Postal Museum|de}} opens * 1996 - [[Caudan Waterfront]] in business.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2013}} * 2000 ** [[AS Port-Louis 2000]] (football club) formed. ** Population: 144,303 metro.<ref name=britannica />
==21st century== * 2002 - Statue of Basdeo Bissoondyal unveiled. * 2006 - [[Bank of Mauritius Tower]] built.<ref name=Emporis>{{cite web |url=https://www.emporis.com/city/100082/port-louis-mauritius/status/all-buildings |title=Mauritius: Port Louis |work=[[Emporis.com]] |publisher=Emporis GmbH |location=Hamburg |accessdate= 23 September 2017 }}</ref> * 2007 - [[Appleby (law firm)|Appleby Mauritius]] in business.[https://www.applebyglobal.com/publication-pdf/site-pdfs/appleby-timeline---april-2016-(2).pdf] * 2008 - {{illm|Musée de l'immigration chinoise|fr}} (museum) opens. * 2010 - Population: 128,483 city; 148,416 metro.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2013}} * 2013 - March-April: Flood.<ref name=bbc /> * 2017 - Daniel Eric Clive Laurent becomes mayor.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.lemauricien.com/article/elections-municipalite-port-louis-daniel-laurent-elu-lord-maire |language=fr |title= Élections, Municipalité de Port-Louis: Daniel Laurent élu lord-maire |work=[[Le Mauricien|Lemauricien.com]] |date=28 June 2017 }}</ref>
